cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about video action recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a new variant of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) and a two-branch neural architecture, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper deals with spatio-temporal relationships and non-local operations, which are relevant to multimedia analysis and retrieval, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are also relevant to neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well.
